13/–¥–µ–∫/22 9:52 AM;62c2c9a2e16ddfe82bdee818;[~accountid:61fc70a9530d2a007147fb52] 

{quote}Are the queued jobs going to start immediately after the required jobs are completed?{quote}

Yes, we wanted to try not to affect the process of loan creation itself. So we will not ‚Äúsacrifice‚Äù any functionality because of this change, it‚Äôs just a technical improvement, which will make it easier technically to handle potential errors, debug different steps. Right now everything is happening inside ‚Äú/loans‚Äù endpoint call, so if something goes wrong.- we end up in a state of DB where it‚Äôs not possible for user to retry it + user has to wait a lot of time while making this endpoint call, and if only one of those things goes wrong - everything goes wrong.

For that we would like to separate these processes in order for them to be more transparent and easy to debug to us, and make these processes more failure-proof.


